lead_paragraph: COMMERCIAL FAILURES.--The Times says, advices from the Mediterranean mention the failure of Messrs. PETER CLARK Co., a firm having establishments at Corfu, Zante, Cephalonia and Patras. Their Habilities are stated at [pound]35,000, and the cause of their stoppage was said to be their connection with Messrs. CASTELLI Co., upon whom they are creditors for [pound]24,000.

headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; BY TELEGRAPH FROM LONDON TO LIVERPOOL. ENGLAND.
